// @check
// @error `for` step is 0
// A range `for` with a literal `step 0` never advances its loop variable — a
// degenerate / infinite loop. The lint pass reports it as an error (B17). The
// parser's empty-range warning deliberately excludes step 0, so this rule covers
// it. `_i` is `_`-prefixed so the loop variable is not flagged.
function loop(): i32 {
  for _i in 0 to 10 step 0 {
    print(1)
  }
  return 0
}
